Functionsยง

  • NT_ERROR
    Evaluates to TRUE if the return value specified by nt_status is an error type (0xC0000000 - 0xFFFFFFFF). This function is taken from ntdef.h in the WDK.
  • NT_INFORMATION
    Evaluates to TRUE if the return value specified by nt_status is an informational type (0x40000000 โ 0x7FFFFFFF). This function is taken from ntdef.h in the WDK.
  • NT_SUCCESS
    Evaluates to TRUE if the return value specified by nt_status is a success type (0 โ 0x3FFFFFFF) or an informational type (0x40000000 โ 0x7FFFFFFF). This function is taken from ntdef.h in the WDK.
  • NT_WARNING
    Evaluates to TRUE if the return value specified by nt_status is a warning type (0x80000000 โ 0xBFFFFFFF). This function is taken from ntdef.h in the WDK.
